{"schema":"algviz/1","title":"Segment Tree (range query + update)","topic":"segment-tree-and-fenwick","code":["private long Query(int v, int lo, int hi, int ql, int qr)","{","    if (qr < lo || hi < ql) return 0;","    if (ql <= lo && hi <= qr) return _seg[v];","    int mid = (lo + hi) / 2;","    return Query(2 * v, lo, mid, ql, qr)","         + Query(2 * v + 1, mid + 1, hi, ql, qr);","}","private void Update(int v, int lo, int hi, int i, int value)","{","    if (lo == hi) { _seg[v] = value; return; }","    int mid = (lo + hi) / 2;","    if (i <= mid) Update(2 * v, lo, mid, i, value);","    else Update(2 * v + 1, mid + 1, hi, i, value);","    _seg[v] = _seg[2 * v] + _seg[2 * v + 1];","}"],"structures":{"seg":{"type":"binaryTree","label":"segment tree (node = range sum)"},"a":{"type":"array1d","label":"a[0..7]  (the data)"}},"frames":[{"line":1,"caption":"Built segment tree over a[0..7]: each node holds the sum of its index range, root [0,7]=36.","note":"A segment tree is a binary tree over index ranges: leaves are single elements, each internal node is the sum of its two children. Stored flat with node v's children at 2v and 2v+1. Height log n, so query and update both touch O(log n) nodes.","vars":{},"result":null,"states":{"seg":{"type":"binaryTree","root":"n1","nodes":[{"key":"n1","value":36,"left":"n2","right":"n3"},{"key":"n2","value":10,"left":"n4","right":"n5"},{"key":"n3","value":26,"left":"n6","right":"n7"},{"key":"n4","value":3,"left":"n8","right":"n9"},{"key":"n5","value":7,"left":"n10","right":"n11"},{"key":"n6","value":11,"left":"n12","right":"n13"},{"key":"n7","value":15,"left":"n14","right":"n15"},{"key":"n8","value":1,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n9","value":2,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n10","value":3,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n11","value":4,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n12","value":5,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n13","value":6,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n14","value":7,"left":null,"right":null},{"key":"n15","value